<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: No Frills Opaque [7 style white split]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8272&amp;p=35391#p35391"><![CDATA[
Hey Pipalou50.<br />It's a bit like Vista search box. I wanted to have blur transparent option, <br />but in order to have blur color on the first column, it makes blurry black text, <br />because Clear Type gets turned off when Fullglass opacity applied, so I skipped it.<br /><br />After all these years we have been coming to this Classic Shell web site,<br />along with the experiments we made at skinning,<br />I'm still dumbfounded by the way glass color masks work. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br /><br />There appear to be different ways of combining red (glass color),<br />and green(white color).<br /><br />It's like there is a nonlinear, and linear curve way, <br />of adding glass/white proportions.<br /><br />On this skin, I opted for adding small amounts of the green mask, to the high red mask value.<br />Example: 255 red with 104 green.<br />If I used 151 red with 104 green, the color saturation amount seen on screen would be different.<br /><br />Here are different examples:<br />To get white color on screen, I can have 0 red mask with 255 green mask,<br />or 255 red mask with 255 green mask.<br />It looks like once total combined red green value goes past 255, <br />the parameters change to nonlinear curve, like a gamma curve.<br /><br />Anyway, I don't want to play around with the skin anymore. <br />I probably should have kept the total combined red green mask values to be no more than 255, <br />for I see I keep getting the same bright color tint, even though the dark taskbar color tint changes.<br /><br />Oh well, every skin is an experiment. Kind of like a lottery. Win a little, lose a lot. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br />As you can see by all my ramblings, I drank some strong coffee this morning. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Feb 06, 2018 8:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
